## Limitations

This analysis is limited by the availability of recent data and the evolving nature of internet access policies worldwide. The debate is ongoing, and new developments in technology and international law may influence future perspectives. Additionally, the interpretation of internet access as a human right may vary significantly across different cultural and legal contexts.